Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 503 290 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19  Today South Africa has exceeded the half a million mark with a cumulative total of 503 290 confirmed COVID-19 cases recorded. Case data Province Total cases for 01 August 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 78782 15,7 Free State 22308 4,4 Gauteng 178119 35,4 KwaZulu-Natal 79607 15,8 Limpopo 8879 1,8 Mpumalanga 14681 2,9 North West 19714 3,9 Northern Cape 4961 1,0 Western Cape 96189 19,1 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 503290 100,0 Testing data The total number of tests conducted to date is 3 001 985 with 42 450 new tests conducted since the last report. Sector Total tested  New tested  PRIVATE 1699574 57% 20397 48% PUBLIC 1302411 43% 22053 52% Total 3001985  42450  Reported deaths and recoveries Regrettably we report 148 new COVID-19 related deaths: 36 from Eastern Cape, 40 from Gauteng, 41 from KwaZulu Natal, 24 from Western Cape and 7 from Northern Cape. This brings the cumulative number of deaths to 8153. We convey our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. The number of recoveries currently stands at 342 461 which translates to a recovery rate of 68%. The provincial breakdown is as follows: Province Deaths Recoveries Eastern Cape 1744 66543 Free State 154 8897 Gauteng 2075 126784 KwaZulu-Natal 844 36358 Limpopo 67 5044 Mpumalanga 78 8124 North West 81 8444 Northern Cape 36 1517 Western Cape 3074 80750 Total 8153 342461 Issued by Department of Health, 1 August 2020  